snippet.textDisplay:
Rangabati is sambalpuri folk song with beautiful deep meaning . In 1979/80 it became first Indian non Hindi song to be broadcasted in BBC London & VOA America. Once a crowd at particular railway station refused to let the train move until Haripal ,the original singer, sang Rangabati song.

Original singer : Padma Shri Jitendra Haripal & his female co-singer Krishna Patel
 Here is the link to original voice -
https://youtu.be/AtIotoQfPgI
English subtitles -
https://www.quora.com/What-is-the-meaning-of-the-Sambalpuri-song-Rangabati
snippet.textOriginal:
